name: The Graeae
description: In Greek mythology, The Graeae, the grey witches, were three sisters who shared one eye and one tooth among them which they took turns using. Perseus stole the eye and forced them to tell the whereabouts of the three objects needed to kill Medusa. Part of The Recursive Series a collection of digital arts inspired by the illustrations of the artist M.C.Escher and mystery noire TV shows from the early 20th century. - Artist: Luiz André Gama - Official Website: www.luizandregama.com  Date of Creation: 2021  Size: 3026x4960px
